    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3000997155" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3000997155" />
    <a title="Cody | CodysBookshelf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf"><img alt="Cody | CodysBookshelf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626597053p2/56352820.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3000997155?book_show_action=true">Oct 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cody | CodysBookshelf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cody | CodysBookshelf" href="/user/show/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf">Cody | CodysBookshelf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780671834845" href="/book/show/6574577-the-vampire-tapestry">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf?shelf=halloween-bingo-2019">halloween-bingo-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/56352820-cody-codysbookshelf?shelf=vintage-horror">vintage-horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3000997155" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18363668475410269278">A shockingly well-written novel, especially for the paperback horror boom era, <i>The Vampire Tapestry</i> has unfortunately fallen into obscurity — and I think that’s a shame. <br/><br/>What one should probably know upfront is this isn’t a “novel” in the conventional sense; it’s five longish stories told in chronological order that portray the reawakening and strange life of our main character, the Vampire. These tales do connect in small and important ways, but the end result is not so much a complete novel bu</span>
  <span id="freeText18363668475410269278" style="display:none">A shockingly well-written novel, especially for the paperback horror boom era, <i>The Vampire Tapestry</i> has unfortunately fallen into obscurity — and I think that’s a shame. <br /><br />What one should probably know upfront is this isn’t a “novel” in the conventional sense; it’s five longish stories told in chronological order that portray the reawakening and strange life of our main character, the Vampire. These tales do connect in small and important ways, but the end result is not so much a complete novel but . . . a tapestry. <br /><br />Also, one should probably know this book isn’t scary, despite what the Stephen King blurb on the front of the ‘81 paperback says. Does a horror book have to be scary? Some say yes, others say no. I don’t care, because the writing herein is at times tragic, and gorgeous, and sensual, and suspenseful. That’s all I need, and more. <br /><br />I am docking a star because the final two stories lost me a bit, especially “A Musical Interlude”. Not bad stuff, it just didn’t live up to the three stories that preceded it. <br /><br /><b>Read for ‘Vampires’ in Halloween Bingo.</b> </span>
  <a data-text-id="18363668475410269278" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


